ivardefs.name: compose
ivardefs.desc: A set of criteria that define the contents of the value set by including or excluding codes selected from the specified code system(s) that the value set draws from. This is also known as the Content Logical Definition (CLD).

ivardefs.name: contact_
ivardefs.desc: Contact details to assist a user in finding and communicating with the publisher.

ivardefs.name: copyright
ivardefs.desc: A copyright statement relating to the value set and/or its contents. Copyright statements are generally legal restrictions on the use and publishing of the value set.

ivardefs.name: date
ivardefs.desc: The date (and optionally time) when the value set was created or revised (e.g. the 'content logical definition').

ivardefs.name: description
ivardefs.desc: A free text natural language description of the value set from a consumer's perspective. The textual description specifies the span of meanings for concepts to be included within the Value Set Expansion, and also may specify the intended use and limitatio

ivardefs.name: expansion
ivardefs.desc: A value set can also be "expanded", where the value set is turned into a simple collection of enumerated codes. This element holds the expansion, if it has been performed.

ivardefs.name: experimental
ivardefs.desc: A Boolean value to indicate that this value set is authored for testing purposes (or education/evaluation/marketing) and is not intended to be used for genuine usage.

ivardefs.name: identifier_
ivardefs.desc: A formal identifier that is used to identify this value set when it is represented in other formats, or referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance.

ivardefs.name: immutable
ivardefs.desc: If this is set to 'true', then no new versions of the content logical definition can be created.  Note: Other metadata might still change.

ivardefs.name: jurisdiction_
ivardefs.desc: A legal or geographic region in which the value set is intended to be used.

ivardefs.name: name
ivardefs.desc: A natural language name identifying the value set. This name should be usable as an identifier for the module by machine processing applications such as code generation.

ivardefs.name: publisher
ivardefs.desc: The name of the organization or individual that published the value set.

ivardefs.name: purpose
ivardefs.desc: Explanation of why this value set is needed and why it has been designed as it has.

ivardefs.name: status
ivardefs.desc: The status of this value set. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content. The status of the value set applies to the value set definition (ValueSet.compose) and the associated ValueSet metadata. Expansions do not have a state.

ivardefs.name: title
ivardefs.desc: A short, descriptive, user-friendly title for the value set.

ivardefs.name: url
ivardefs.desc: An absolute URI that is used to identify this value set when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance; also called its canonical identifier. This SHOULD be globally unique and SHOULD be a literal address at which at which an autho

ivardefs.name: useContext_
ivardefs.desc: The content was developed with a focus and intent of supporting the contexts that are listed. These contexts may be general categories (gender, age, ...) or may be references to specific programs (insurance plans, studies, ...) and may be used to assist w

ivardefs.name: version
ivardefs.desc: The identifier that is used to identify this version of the value set when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or instance. This is an arbitrary value managed by the value set author and is not expected to be globally unique. For example, i

properties.desc: A ValueSet resource instance specifies a set of codes drawn from one or more code systems, intended for use in a particular context. Value sets link between [[[CodeSystem]]] definitions and their use in [coded elements](terminologies.html).
